The making of cricket package yorkr - Part 3

Tinniam V Ganesh

March 16, 2016

Introduction

This is the 3rd part of my cricket package yorkr in R. In my 2 earlier posts

  1. The making of cricket package yorkr - Part 1. In this post I analyze the performance of team in a ODI match. The batting and bowling performances of the team were analyzed. This post also performed analyses of a country in all matches against another country for e.g. India vs All matches of Australia. The best performers with the bat and ball were determined, the best batting partenrships, the detailed performances of the bowlers of India and Australia in the confrontation was also analyzed.

b.The making of cricket package yorkr - Part 2 This post includes all ODI matches between a country and others. For obvious reasons I have chosen India and selected all ODI matches played by India with other countries. This included batting and bowling performances of the country against all oppositions.

As mentioned in my earlier posts the data is taken from Cricsheet

In this post I look at individual performances of batsmen and bowlers in ODIs. For this post I have chose Virat Kohli & Mahendra Singh Dhoni from India and AB Devilliers from South Africa. For bowling analyses I have selected RA Jadeja, Harbhajan Singh and Mitchell Johnson

library(dplyr)

p1 <-batsmanRunsVsDeliveries(kohli,"Kohli")

grid.arrange(p1,p2,p3, ncol=3)

kohli46 <- select(kohli,batsman,ballsPlayed,fours,sixes,runs)
p1 <- batsmanFoursSixes(kohli46,"Kohli")
dhoni46 <- select(dhoni,batsman,ballsPlayed,fours,sixes,runs)
p2 <- batsmanFoursSixes(dhoni46,"Dhoni")
devilliers46 <- select(devilliers,batsman,ballsPlayed,fours,sixes,runs)
p3 <- batsmanFoursSixes(devilliers46, "De Villiers")
grid.arrange(p1,p2,p3, ncol=3)

p1 <-batsmanDismissals(kohli,"Kohli")
